COMMITTEE ON BUDGET, APPROPRIATIONS AND FINANCE
BILL NO. 36-0122
Thirty-Sixth Legislature of the Virgin Islands
July 23, 2025
An act amending title 3 Virgin Islands Code, chapter 27, section 711 and chapter 28a, section
760, by requiring the Government Employees Retirement System to discontinue making
disability retirement annuity payments to a member who resumes any employment
PROPOSED BY: Senator Alma Francis Heyliger
1 Be it enacted by the Legislature of the Virgin Islands:
2 SECTION 1. Title 3 Virgin Islands Code is amended as follows:
3 (a) chapter 27, section 711 is amended by striking all the language in subsection (b) and
4 inserting the following new language:
5 “The System shall discontinue making duty disability retirement annuity payments
6 or nonduty disability retirement annuity payments to a member who resumes any
7 employment.”
8 (b) chapter 28a, section 760 is amended by striking all the language in subsection (b)
9 and inserting the following new language:
10 “The System shall discontinue making duty disability retirement annuity payments
11 or nonduty disability retirement annuity payments to a member who resumes any
12 employment.”

